Program: Last Word
Title: Lord Newton, Jocky Wilson, Jennifer Longford, Earl Scruggs and Abdullahi Yusuf Ahmed
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01dvzgf
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 1 Apr 2012
Matthew Bannister on: The Tory politician Lord Newton - a respected Minister of Health and Secretary of State for social security. Edwina Currie tells us why she confided in him about her affair with John Major. The darts player Jocky Wilson - a Scottish hero to the poet Ian Macmillan who pays tribute. Abdullahi Yusuf Ahmed, the warlord who became President of Somalia but couldn't stop the country's tribal and religious violence Jennifer Longford, daughter of Lloyd George's mistress - but was Lloyd George her father? And banjo player extraordinaire Earl Scruggs - Whispering Bob Harris pays tribute to the bluegrass pioneer.. Show less